# Bug Report

createIndex arguments appear to be swapped, causing index creation to fail

Description

After updating to mongoose@8.15.1 (MongoDB 7.0.14 in my environment), creating indexes that use index options (eg. background, unique, collation, etc.) fails with MongoDB errors indicating the index key pattern is invalid — the options object is being treated as the key pattern.

Minimal reproduction

Save and run this simple script (replace the connection string with a working MongoDB URI):

const mongoose = require('mongoose');

async function run() {
  await mongoose.connect('mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/testdb');

  const schema = new mongoose.Schema({ name: String });
  // trying to create an index with options
  schema.index({ name: 1 }, { background: true, name: 'background_true' });

  const Model = mongoose.model('Person', schema);

  try {
    await Model.init();
    console.log('index created');
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
  } finally {
    await mongoose.disconnect();
  }
}

run();

Expected
- The index is created successfully, or at worst, a handled Mongoose error indicating invalid index options.
- The index key pattern sent to the server should be { name: 1 }.

Actual
- The server receives the index key pattern as the options object (eg. { background: true }) and returns an error:

MongoServerError: Error in specification { name: "background_true", key: { background: true } } :: caused by :: Values in v:2 index key pattern cannot be of type bool. Only numbers > 0, numbers < 0, and strings are allowed.
    at Connection.sendCommand (node_modules/mongodb/lib/cmap/connection.js:299:27)
    at process.processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:95:5)
    ...

Additional symptoms
- Multiple tests / index creation paths fail with the same error.
- Some behavior around unique/index validation also appears broken because the wrong key pattern gets sent to MongoDB (duplicate key errors are not observed where expected).

Environment
- mongoose@8.15.1
- MongoDB 7.0.14 (downloaded automatically in my setup)
- Node.js v18+ (typical dev environment)

Notes
- This appears to affect any index creation where options are passed alongside index fields (background, unique, collation, etc.).
- I can provide more traces/logs if helpful.

---

The repository is at /workspace. Fix the bug, test it, then call submit().

